Marketing and communications coordinator at Life Entabeni, Lara Richards, said; "The demonstration showed a life-threatening emergency where two people were entrapped in a mangled vehicle. The Jaws of Life and other hydraulic equipment was used to extricate the patients while scene safety was maintained and while the paramedics intervened with life-saving support."

 


Richards said the team will then demonstrate how a patient is loaded into an ambulance and handed over the trauma staff at the hospital. 

 


Despite the rain this morning, the teams worked fervently to rescue the "injured" patients. 
We honour our men and women of trauma units across SA. 

